 What we want to accomplish and why we need you? 
 
Haptik is one of the world's largest Conversational AI companies, having reached over 100 million devices, and processed over 2 billion conversations till date. Haptik has been at the forefront of the paradigm shift of interaction from clicks to conversations. We have built a robust set of technology and tools that can enable any kind of conversational application. With a 200 + member strong team, including some of the finest minds in Artificial Intelligence, Haptik is truly poised to lead the Conversational AI revolution. We are building bots for all sizes of enterprises, big and small - come and join us! 
 
We are a full-stack conversational AI company from building products to delivering bots for our clients. We are looking for an ‚ÄúIntegration Engineer‚Äù to believe in this mission and to help develop high-quality chatbots for our clients. 
 
What will you do every day? 
 
As an Integration Engineer, you will be working in a fast-paced agile environment where you will use your knowledge of backend web technologies and combine them with your understanding of Haptik‚Äôs bot building tool to deliver awesome chatbots for our clients. You will be part of a talented team of Program Managers, Engineering Managers, QA Engineers, UX, and Content Specialists. 
 
Ok, you're sold, but what are we looking for in the perfect candidate? 
 Use Haptik platform tools and collaborate with the conversation design team to build conversational flows, both chat and voice-based, with amazing user experience 
 Be comfortable working with multiple integrations in parallel and clients to understand their requirements and implementation of APIs 
 Integrate and develop various different web-based APIs and system to build logic flows for chatbots 
 Maintain up-to-date knowledge of technology standards, industry trends, emerging technologies, and software development best practices 
 Participate in code reviews, automated and functional testing, and other aspects of our quality assurance process (including client validation) 
 Create professional technical documentations and present for internal and external use 
 Model database architecture for performance and scalability 
 Participate in a scrum-based, agile development team 
 Requirements* 
 Must have a Bachelor's or higher degree in computer engineering, IIT/NIT graduate preferred. 
 2-3 years of experience in developing and integrating scalable products 
 Good knowledge of python and Django framework 
 Must have modeled database schemas for large scale applications using MySQL, Mongo, etc 
 Knowledge of RabbitMQ, Redis, Elasticsearch, and Docker is a plus. 
 Excellent written and verbal communication skills 
 Exceptional organizational skills and time management abilities 
 Must be a hustler and should have an entrepreneurial mindset 
 Should be comfortable working in a fast paced environment, habitual of quick turnaround and take ownership of the project in question 
 Bring a focused attitude to work with a strong attention to detail 
 
 Requirements is such a strong word. We don‚Äôt necessarily expect to find a candidate that has done everything listed, but you should be able to make a credible case that you‚Äôve done most of it and are ready for the challenge of adding some new things to your resume. 
 
Tell me more about Haptik 
 On a roll: Announced major strategic partnership with Jio. 
